# Membership and Attendance Tracking System

A Java + MySQL-based system to manage demographic records, track monthly attendance, and monitor membership validity for community members.

---

## üìÇ Project Structure

- `src/` ‚Äì Java source files
- `pwdCares.sql` ‚Äì MySQL schema + sample data *(optional if using built-in initializer)*

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Features

- Member registration with complete demographic and household information
- Medical history and medication tracking
- Attendance tracking per member per month
- Yearly attendance summaries
- Membership status tracking (`Expired`, `Renewed`, `Deceased`, `Alive`)
- ID validity checks and renewal system
- Auto-initialization of the database (no need for manual import)
- Default admin account created on first run

---

## üóÉÔ∏è Database Schema

The system auto-generates the database and tables via `DatabaseInitializer.java`.
If you prefer manual setup, use `pwdCares.sql`.

### Tables:
- `admins` ‚Äì Admin login credentials
- `members` ‚Äì Main profile sheet
- `members_household` ‚Äì Family composition
- `members_conditions` ‚Äì Health conditions (checkboxes)
- `members_medications` ‚Äì Up to 15 meds per member
- `attendance` ‚Äì Per date member attendance

---

## üíæ Default Database Credentials

The system uses the following default MySQL credentials:

- **Username**: `root`
- **Password**: `1234`

> üîß **Custom MySQL Setup?**
> If your local MySQL username/password differs, open `src/db/database.java` and update:
`
private static final String USERNAME = "your_mysql_username";
private static final String PASSWORD = "your_mysql_password";
`
## ‚öôÔ∏è Java Setup Instructions

### 1. Prerequisites
- Java 8 or higher (Java 24 recommended)
- IntelliJ IDEA (or any IDE)
- MySQL Server (Workbench optional)

### 2. Example DB Connection
```java
Connection conn = DriverManager.getConnection(
    "jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/membership_system", "root", "your_password");
```

### 3. First-Time Run
- Create the membership_system schema (if not exists)
- Create all required tables
- Insert a default admin user:
   Username: admin
   Password: 1234

## üìå Usage Notes
- `status`, `civilStatus`,and `sex` columns are `ENUM`, synced with GUI dropdowns
- Attendance dropdown is dynamically populated from distinct attendance years
- Auto-expiration reminders and renewal checks are handled in SQL or Java

